import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Normal Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual')
    ax.plot(data['day'], data['forecast'], label='Forecast')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("How does the 'actual' value compare to the 'forecast' value?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['record'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['record'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['record'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['record'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['record'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Record')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'record' values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['normal', 'actual'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['normal'], data['actual'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Normal')
    ax.set_ylabel('Actual')
    ax.set_title("What is the relationship between 'normal' and 'actual' values?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
